        %p Welcome to my page!

        %p My name is George and I like to think about optimisation problems.

        %p I am currently a machine learning researcher with Citadel, London. I obtained my Ph.D. in machine learning from the Department of Computing, at Imperial College London (2013-2017). My work mostly focused in the unification of component analysis techniques with deep learning, predominantly for unsupervised and semi-supervised applications.

        %p The application areas I touched upon are that of 3d reconstruction, object alignment,  facial biometrics, and emotion recognition.

        %p
          I am also lucky enough to be a recipient of the prestigious
          %a{style: "color:black;text-decoration:underline", href: "https://research.googleblog.com/2017/04/announcing-2017-google-phd-fellows-for.html"} Google Fellowship in Machine Perception, Speech Technology, and Computer Vision.

        %br
        %br

